When using VS Code via remote tunnels, users encounter a spurious "GitHub Authentication - Reload required" dialog that appears even when the `github-authentication.useElectronFetch` setting hasn't actually changed.

![GitHub Authentication - Reload required dialog](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/91cf9e01-76bc-4a38-8327-00161bab5bea)

## Root Cause

In remote scenarios, the `onDidChangeConfiguration` event fires for `github-authentication.useElectronFetch` even when the configuration value remains the same. This causes the reload dialog to appear unnecessarily, creating a poor user experience.

## Solution

Applied the same defensive pattern already used in the same file for the `github-enterprise.uri` configuration:

1. Store the initial configuration value before setting up the listener
2. Compare the old and new values when the configuration change event fires
3. Only show the reload dialog if the value has actually changed

```typescript
// Before: Always showed dialog on any configuration event
context.subscriptions.push(vscode.workspace.onDidChangeConfiguration(async e => {
    if (e.affectsConfiguration('github-authentication.useElectronFetch')) {
        // Always showed dialog
    }
}));

// After: Only show dialog when value actually changes
let beforeFetchSetting = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration('github-authentication').get<boolean>('useElectronFetch');
context.subscriptions.push(vscode.workspace.onDidChangeConfiguration(async e => {
    if (e.affectsConfiguration('github-authentication.useElectronFetch')) {
        const afterFetchSetting = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration('github-authentication').get<boolean>('useElectronFetch');
        if (beforeFetchSetting !== afterFetchSetting) {
            beforeFetchSetting = afterFetchSetting;
            // Only show dialog when value actually changed
        }
    }
}));
```

This change is minimal (5 lines added) and follows the exact same pattern already established in the same file for handling the `github-enterprise.uri` configuration changes.

