Background terminals were not displaying auto-approve indicators when commands were automatically approved by rules, unlike foreground terminals which correctly showed messages like "_Auto approved by rule `npm`_".

The issue was in the `runInTerminalTool.ts` background execution path, which only returned `content` without including the `toolResultMessage` that contains the auto-approve information.

**Before:**
```typescript
// Background terminals
return {
    content: [{
        kind: 'text',
        value: resultText,
    }]
};
```

**After:**
```typescript
// Background terminals now include auto-approve info
let toolResultMessage: string | undefined;
if (toolSpecificData.autoApproveInfo) {
    toolResultMessage = toolSpecificData.autoApproveInfo.value;
}

return {
    toolResultMessage: toolResultMessage ? new MarkdownString(toolResultMessage) : undefined,
    content: [{
        kind: 'text',
        value: resultText,
    }]
};
```

This change ensures background terminals display the same auto-approve indicators as foreground terminals, providing consistent user feedback about which rules were used to automatically approve commands.

